      <scopecontent id="aspace_2106eb4bc978c4768bf5dd9a02f85dbc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Tarleton Family Papers consist of letters, photographs, and miscellaneous items of the Tarleton and Lightfoot families of Alabama, primarily from the Civil War era. Most of the letters were written by Robert Tarleton to his mother and his fiancée and wife while he was at military camps during the war and doing business away from home in the early years of Reconstruction. The photographs show Tarleton and his wife, their parents, and a few other people.</p>
         <p>The Tarleton Family Papers were given to Yale University Library by Mr. And Mrs. Robert M. Tarleton and by Mrs. A. R. Colvin in 1940 and 1942.</p>
         <p>Additional Tarleton family photographs are located in the Historical Picture Collection (MS 713):</p>
         <p>- Margaret (Brack) Tarleton</p>
         <p>- Robert Tarleton</p>
         <p>- Robert Tarleton and another young man</p>
         <p>- Captain Jack and Sarah (Mrs. Jack) Eggleston</p>
         <p>- Alfred Ross, borther of Sarah Bee (Ross) Lightfoot</p>
         <p>- Unidentified young man</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_059e786fb100294a3c62cf1cc00f4e09">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Robert Tarleton (1838-1868): doctor; studied medicine in New York City; served in the Confederate Army during the Civil War; taken prisoner and escaped, 1864.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_665afbcb11d002f29186079d8874a1c0">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
